{"id":4192,"date":"2016-06-30T11:27:32","date_gmt":"2016-06-30T10:27:32","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/srt-marine.com\/?p=4192"},"modified":"2017-02-06T10:37:30","modified_gmt":"2017-02-06T10:37:30","slug":"srt-ecuador-navy-work-together-benefit-local-fishing-communities","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/srt-marine.com\/srt-ecuador-navy-work-together-benefit-local-fishing-communities\/","title":{"rendered":"SRT and Ecuador Navy work together for the benefit of local fishing communities"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Fifty fishermen in Esmeraldas were given brand new, high quality fishing nets today to help them recover from the devastating earthquake in April 2016. The nets were donated by SRT Marine Technology of the UK who has been working with the national marine authorities to improve maritime management, safety and security.<\/p>\n<p>Fishing is a critical industry of national importance, providing jobs for tens of thousands of people, a valuable and popular food source for the Ecuador people and valuable economic contribution to the national economy. Improved technology, equipment and partnerships between the fishing communities and national authorities will help fishermen to thrive and in turn generate benefit for the national economy.<\/p>\n<p>Through its extensive on the ground work with Ecuador national marine agencies, SRT Marine Technology has begun to know and understand the Ecuador maritime domain and fishing communities. SRT saw, first hand, the effects of the earthquake and commensurate with SRT\u2019s sustainable business practices wanted to help. This has resulted in SRT working with local partners to make today\u2019s donation of nets to fishermen in the most need of assistance.<\/p>\n<p>Simon Tucker, SRT CEO said: \u201cThrough our work in Ecuador we have formed many friendships which transcend business. We were in Ecuador when the earthquake struck and have seen first-hand how fishermen have been affected and, quite simply, we wanted to try and contribute to help our friends.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-4193\" src=\"https:\/\/srt-marine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/SRT-works-with-Ecuador-Navy-to-help-fishermen-in-Esmeraldas.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"543\" height=\"364\" srcset=\"https:\/\/srt-marine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/SRT-works-with-Ecuador-Navy-to-help-fishermen-in-Esmeraldas.png 543w, https:\/\/srt-marine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/SRT-works-with-Ecuador-Navy-to-help-fishermen-in-Esmeraldas-300x201.png 300w, https:\/\/srt-marine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/SRT-works-with-Ecuador-Navy-to-help-fishermen-in-Esmeraldas-127x85.png 127w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 543px) 100vw, 543px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Fifty fishermen in Esmeraldas were given brand new, high quality fishing nets today to help them recover from the devastating earthquake in April 2016. The nets were donated by SRT Marine Technology of the UK who has been working with the national marine authorities to improve maritime management, safety and security. Fishing is a critical [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_genesis_hide_title":false,"_genesis_hide_breadcrumbs":false,"_genesis_hide_singular_image":false,"_genesis_hide_footer_widgets":false,"_genesis_custom_body_class":"","_genesis_custom_post_class":"","_genesis_layout":""},"categories":[5],"tags":[],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v20.9 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>SRT and Ecuador Navy work together for the benefit of local fishing communities - SRT Marine Systems plc<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https